fields.name: Access Category That Does Not Exist
fields.description: Check that an error does not occur when trying to access a category page that doesn't exist

fields.name: Category Form Being Displayed Correctly
fields.description:
Check whether '

Add a Category

'; 'Please enter the category name.'; 'id="id_name" maxlength="128" name="name" type="text"' ; and 'type="submit" name="submit" value="Create Category"' all appear on the 'add_category' page.

fields.name: Add Page Form Displaying Correctly
fields.description: Checks whether 'Please enter the title of the page.' ; 'Please enter the URL of the page.' ; 'id="id_title" maxlength="128" name="title" type="text"' ;  'id="id_url" maxlength="200" name="url" type="url"' ; and 'type="submit" name="submit" value="Add Page"' all appear on the add page page.

fields.name: Category Page Contains Link To Add Pages
fields.description: Check whether the category pages contain a link to add a new page to that category.

fields.name: Index Page Contains Link to Add Category
fields.description: Check whether there is text with a link on the index page which takes you to the add category page.

fields.name: Link To Add Pages Only Appears On Valid Categories
fields.description: Checks that the link to add a page to the category only appears if the category actually exists in the database.

fields.name: User Profile Model Working Correctly
fields.description: Creates a new user and checks whether the user is saved correctly to the database.

fields.name: Login Form Displayed Correctly
fields.description:
Checks if the login page contains '

Login to Rango

' followed by the username and password labels/inputs followed by a submit button.

fields.name: Login Form Provides Error Reporting
fields.description: Test if 'Invalid login details supplied.' appears if wrong user details are inputted to the login form.

fields.name: Login Redirects To Index
fields.description: Check whether a signed in user visiting the login page will be redirected to the index page.

fields.name: Registration Form Displaying Correctly
fields.description:
Check if the register page contains 'register here!
' followed by an instance of the user_form and profile_form.

fields.name: Uploading Profile Images Working Correctly
fields.description: Creates a new user with a profile image, then checks the media path to see if the image is stored and checks if the user model links to the correct image.

fields.name: About Contains Create Message (3)
fields.description: Check if  'Rango says here is the about page' appears on the about page.

fields.name: Index Page Contains Hello Message (3)
fields.description: Check whether 'Rango says' appears on the index page.

fields.name: Index Page Displays Number Of Accesses and Last Access
fields.description: Check whether the index page contains the number of times a user has accessed the page and the time of their last access.

fields.name: About Page Shows Number of Visits
fields.description: Check if the about page shows the correct number of times a user has visited the page.

fields.name: Index Page Displays Number Of Visits
fields.description: Check whether the index page displays the correct number of visits for a user.

fields.name: Number Of Visits Exists In Index Context Dictionary
fields.description: Checks whether the number of times a user has visited is being passed to the index template in the index view context dictionary.

fields.name: About Page Contains Image (2)
fields.description: Check whether 'img src="/static/images/' appears in about.html.

fields.name: About Contains Create Message (2)
fields.description: Check if 'This tutorial has been put together by' appears on the about page.

fields.name: About Page Using Template (3)
fields.description: Check if the 'about.html' template is being used for the about page.

fields.name: About Contains Create Message
fields.description: Check if 'This tutorial has been put together by' appears on the about page.

fields.name: About Page Using Template (2)
fields.description: Check if the 'about.html' template is being used for the about page.

fields.name: About Page Contains Image
fields.description: Check if 'img' appears in 'about.html'.

fields.name: Index Contains Image
fields.description: Check whether 'img' appears in 'index.html'

fields.name: Index Page Contains Hello Message (2)
fields.description: Check whether 'Rango says' appears on the index page.

fields.name: Admin Interface For Pages Include Category and URL
fields.description: Check whether 'category' and 'url' exists in PageAdmin.

fields.name: Python Category Exists (2)
fields.description: Checks whether the Python category exists in the database.

fields.name: Python Category Has 64 Likes (2)
fields.description: Tests whether the Python category has 64 likes.

fields.name: Python Category Has 128 Views (2)
fields.description: Checks whether the Python category has 128 views.

fields.name: Test View Has Title (2)
fields.description: Checks if the html '<title>' and '</title>' tags appear on the index page.

fields.name: Category Slug Field Working
fields.description: Creates a Category named 'how do i create a slug in Django' is given a slug field containing 'how-do-i-create-a-slug-field'.

fields.name: Serving Static Files (2)
fields.description: Checks whether the file 'images/rango.jpg' exists.

fields.name: Index Page Contains Hello Message (2)
fields.description: Check whether 'Rango says' appears on the index page.

fields.name: Index Page Has Title (2)
fields.description: Checks if the html '<title>' and '</title>' tags appear in index.html

fields.name: Index Page Using Template (2)
fields.description: Checks if the index page is being displayed using a template

fields.name: Rango Picture Displayed On Index (2)
fields.description: Tests whether 'img src="/static/images/rango.jpg' appears on index page once rendered.

fields.name: Python Category Exists
fields.description: Checks whether the Python category exists in the database.

fields.name: Python Category Has 64 Likes
fields.description: Tests whether the Python category has 64 likes.

fields.name: Python Category Has 128 Views
fields.description: Checks whether the Python category has 128 views.

fields.name: Create A New Category
fields.description: Creates a new category and checks to see if it was saved correctly to the database.

fields.name: Creating Pages for Categories
fields.description: Creates pages for a category and tests whether they are being saved properly to the database.

fields.name: Population Script Updating Database
fields.description: Tests whether the population script is creating a Category named "Python" with 128 views and 64 likes; a Category named "Django" with 64 views and 32 likes; and a Category named "Other Frameworks" with 32 views and 16 likes.

fields.name: Base Template Exists
fields.description: Checks whether the 'base.html' exists at ' TEMPLATE_DIR + /rango/base.html'.

fields.name: Base Template Links To Index
fields.description: Tests whether a link to the index page exists in the base template.

fields.name: Every Page Extending Base Template
fields.description: Tests whether each page is extending the 'base.html' template.

fields.name: Page Titles Being Displayed
fields.description: Tests each page to see if they all have a title being displayed.

fields.name: Add Page URL Displayed on Category Page
fields.description: Checks whether the URL for 'add_page' is being displayed on each category page.

fields.name: Index Page Showing More URLs When Logged In
fields.description: Checks whether the 'add_category', 'restricted', 'logout' and 'about' page URLs are displayed on the index page when a user is logged in.

fields.name: Index Page Hiding Some URLs When Not Logged In
fields.description: Tests whether only the 'register', 'login' and 'about' page URLs are appearing when user is not logged in.

fields.name: Each Category Contains Slug Field
fields.description: Tests whether a generated category named "Test Category" will be given the slug field "test-category".

fields.name: Category View Using Context Dictionary
fields.description: Checks the data in the context dictionary being passed into the show_category view contains the same data as the database.

fields.name: Category Page Displays Does Not Exists Message
fields.description: Tests whether "does not exist!" appears on the category page if it does not exist.

fields.name: Category Page Displays Empty Message
fields.description: Checks whether the category page will display "No pages currently in category." if there are no pages associated with it.

fields.name: Category Pages Displaying Pages
fields.description: Checks to see if each category page is displaying the pages associated with it.

fields.name: Category Page Using Template
fields.description: Checks to see whether the categories pages are being rendered using a template.

fields.name: Link To Categories From Index Page
fields.description: Check whether the index page contains a link to each of the five most liked categories.

fields.name: Index View Using Context Dictionary
fields.description: Tests that if the database if empty, the context dictionary in the index view is also empty. Also checks that if the database is not empty, the data in the context dictionary matches that of the data in the database.

fields.name: Index Displaying Five Most Liked Categories
fields.description: Checks whether the index page is displaying the five categories with the most likes.

fields.name: Index Displaying Five Most Viewed Pages
fields.description: Checks whether the index page is displaying the top five viewed pages or not.

fields.name: Displays No Categories Message On Index Page
fields.description: Checks to see whether "There are no categories present." is displayed on the index page.

fields.name: Static Image Displayed On About Page
fields.description: Checks whether a static image is being displayed on the about page.

fields.name: About Page Using Template
fields.description: Checks to see whether the about page is being rendered using a template.

fields.name: Cat Image Displayed On About Page
fields.description: Checks if media/cat.jpg is being displayed on the about page.

fields.name: Index Page Using Template
fields.description: Checks to see whether the index page is being rendered using a template.

fields.name: Rango Picture Displayed On Index Page
fields.description: Tests to see whether the rango.jpg image is displayed on the index page.

fields.name: Serving Static Files On Index Page
fields.description: Searches to see if using static media properly by looking for rango.jpg.

fields.name: Index Page Has Title
fields.description: Checks to see whether the index view is using the title tag correctly.
